var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"location":"guide/responses_api/#responses_guide","page":"Responses API","title":"Responses API","text":"The Responses API is OpenAI's newer, more flexible alternative to Chat Completions. Key advantages include built-in tools (web search, file search), stateless multi-turn via previous_response_id, and reasoning support for O-series models.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Basic-Usage","page":"Responses API","title":"Basic Usage","text":"The simplest call — just a string:\n\njulia> result = respond(\"Explain Julia's multiple dispatch in 2-3 sentences.\")\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Julia's multiple dispatch means a function can have many method definitions, and Julia chooses which one to run based on the types of *all* arguments in a call (not just the first). This makes it easy to write generic code while still getting specialized, high-performance behavior for specific type combinations.\"\n\njulia> result.response.id\n\"resp_00e791c82448c27d006990c7a81de88194975ba388932de6b8\"\n\njulia> result.response.status\n\"completed\"\n\njulia> result.response.model\n\"gpt-5.2-2025-12-11\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#The-Respond-Type","page":"Responses API","title":"The Respond Type","text":"For full control, construct a Respond object:\n\nusing UniLM\nusing JSON\n\nr = Respond(\n    model=\"gpt-5.2\",\n    input=\"Explain monads simply\",\n    instructions=\"You are a functional programming expert. Be concise.\",\n    temperature=0.5,\n    max_output_tokens=500,\n)\nprintln(\"Model: \", r.model)\nprintln(\"Request body:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(r))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Instructions-(System-Prompt)","page":"Responses API","title":"Instructions (System Prompt)","text":"Unlike Chat Completions where you push a system Message, the Responses API uses the instructions parameter:\n\njulia> result = respond(\n           \"Translate to French: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.\",\n           instructions=\"You are a professional translator. Respond only with the translation.\"\n       )\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Le rapide renard brun saute par-dessus le chien paresseux.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Structured-Input","page":"Responses API","title":"Structured Input","text":"For multimodal inputs, use InputMessage with content helpers:\n\n# Text-only structured input\nmsgs = [\n    InputMessage(role=\"system\", content=\"You analyze images.\"),\n    InputMessage(role=\"user\", content=[\n        input_text(\"What do you see in this image?\"),\n        input_image(\"https://example.com/photo.jpg\"),\n    ]),\n]\nr = Respond(input=msgs, model=\"gpt-5.2\")\nprintln(\"Input is structured: \", r.input isa Vector)\nprintln(\"Number of input messages: \", length(r.input))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Input-Helpers","page":"Responses API","title":"Input Helpers","text":"Function Purpose\ninput_text Text content part\ninput_image Image URL content part\ninput_file File (URL or ID) content part","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Multi-Turn-Conversations","page":"Responses API","title":"Multi-Turn Conversations","text":"Chain requests using previous_response_id — no need to re-send the full history:\n\njulia> r1 = respond(\"Tell me a one-liner programming joke.\", instructions=\"Be concise.\")\n\njulia> output_text(r1)\n\"There are only 10 kinds of people in the world: those who understand binary and those who don't.\"\n\njulia> r2 = respond(\"Explain why that's funny, in one sentence.\", previous_response_id=r1.response.id)\n\njulia> output_text(r2)\n\"It's funny because \\\"10\\\" looks like ten in decimal but equals two in binary, so it sets up a nerdy misdirection that only people who know binary immediately get.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Built-in-Tools","page":"Responses API","title":"Built-in Tools","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Web-Search","page":"Responses API","title":"Web Search","text":"julia> result = respond(\n           \"What is the latest stable release of the Julia programming language?\",\n           tools=[web_search()]\n       )\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"The latest **stable** release of the Julia programming language is **Julia v1.12.5**.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#File-Search","page":"Responses API","title":"File Search","text":"result = respond(\n    \"Find information about error handling\",\n    tools=[file_search([\"vs_abc123\"])]\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Function-Tools","page":"Responses API","title":"Function Tools","text":"weather_tool = function_tool(\n    \"get_weather\",\n    \"Get current weather for a location\",\n    parameters=Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"description\" => \"City name\")\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"location\"]\n    )\n)\nprintln(\"Tool name: \", weather_tool.name)\nprintln(\"Tool JSON: \", JSON.json(JSON.lower(weather_tool)))\n\njulia> result = respond(\"What's the weather in Tokyo? Use celsius.\", tools=[weather_tool])\n\njulia> calls = function_calls(result)\n\njulia> calls[1][\"name\"]\n\"get_weather\"\n\njulia> JSON.parse(calls[1][\"arguments\"])\n{\n  \"location\": \"Tokyo\",\n  \"unit\": \"celsius\"\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Reasoning-(O-Series-Models)","page":"Responses API","title":"Reasoning (O-Series Models)","text":"For models like o3 that support extended reasoning:\n\nr = Respond(\n    input=\"Prove that √2 is irrational\",\n    model=\"o3\",\n    reasoning=Reasoning(effort=\"high\", summary=\"detailed\")\n)\nprintln(\"Model: \", r.model)\nprintln(\"Reasoning effort: \", r.reasoning.effort)\nprintln(JSON.json(r))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Structured-Output","page":"Responses API","title":"Structured Output","text":"Force JSON-conformant output:\n\n# JSON Schema format\nfmt = json_schema_format(\n    \"colors\",\n    \"A list of colors\",\n    Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"colors\" => Dict(\n                \"type\" => \"array\",\n                \"items\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n            )\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"colors\"]\n    ),\n    strict=true\n)\nprintln(\"Format type: \", fmt.format.type)\nprintln(\"Schema name: \", fmt.format.name)\n\njulia> result = respond(\n           \"List Julia, Python, and Rust with their release year and primary paradigm.\",\n           text=fmt\n       )\n\njulia> JSON.parse(output_text(result))\n{\n  \"languages\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Julia\",\n      \"year\": 2012,\n      \"paradigm\": \"Multi-paradigm (scientific/numerical, functional, concurrent)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Python\",\n      \"year\": 1991,\n      \"paradigm\": \"Multi-paradigm (object-oriented, imperative, functional)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Rust\",\n      \"year\": 2010,\n      \"paradigm\": \"Multi-paradigm (systems programming, functional, imperative)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Response-Accessors","page":"Responses API","title":"Response Accessors","text":"result = respond(\"Hello!\")\n\nif result isa ResponseSuccess\n    r = result.response\n\n    output_text(result)      # full text output\n    function_calls(result)   # Vector of function call Dicts (empty if none)\n\n    r.id                     # \"resp_00e791c8...\"\n    r.status                 # \"completed\"\n    r.model                  # \"gpt-5.2-2025-12-11\"\n    r.output                 # full output array\n    r.usage                  # Dict with token counts\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#Managing-Stored-Responses","page":"Responses API","title":"Managing Stored Responses","text":"# Retrieve a previously stored response\nresult = get_response(\"resp_00e791c82448c27d...\")\n\n# Delete a stored response\ndelete_response(\"resp_00e791c82448c27d...\")\n\n# List input items for a response\nitems = list_input_items(\"resp_00e791c82448c27d...\", limit=50)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/responses_api/#See-Also","page":"Responses API","title":"See Also","text":"Respond — full type reference\nResponseObject — response structure\nTool Calling — detailed tool calling guide\nStreaming — streaming with do-blocks","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/respond_structured/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> fmt = json_schema_format(\n           \"languages\", \"A list of programming languages\",\n           Dict(\n               \"type\" => \"object\",\n               \"properties\" => Dict(\n                   \"languages\" => Dict(\n                       \"type\" => \"array\",\n                       \"items\" => Dict(\n                           \"type\" => \"object\",\n                           \"properties\" => Dict(\n                               \"name\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\"),\n                               \"year\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"integer\"),\n                               \"paradigm\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n                           ),\n                           \"required\" => [\"name\", \"year\", \"paradigm\"],\n                           \"additionalProperties\" => false\n                       )\n                   )\n               ),\n               \"required\" => [\"languages\"],\n               \"additionalProperties\" => false\n           ),\n           strict=true\n       )\n\njulia> result = respond(\n           \"List Julia, Python, and Rust with their release year and primary paradigm.\",\n           text=fmt\n       )\n\njulia> JSON.parse(output_text(result))\n{\n  \"languages\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Julia\",\n      \"year\": 2012,\n      \"paradigm\": \"Multi-paradigm (scientific/numerical, functional, concurrent)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Python\",\n      \"year\": 1991,\n      \"paradigm\": \"Multi-paradigm (object-oriented, imperative, functional)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Rust\",\n      \"year\": 2010,\n      \"paradigm\": \"Multi-paradigm (systems programming, functional, imperative)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/image_generation/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> result = generate_image(\n           \"A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book\",\n           size=\"1024x1024\",\n           quality=\"medium\"\n       )\n\njulia> result isa ImageSuccess\ntrue\n\njulia> length(image_data(result))\n1\n\njulia> length(image_data(result)[1])  # base64 string length\n2654660\n\njulia> result.response.data[1].revised_prompt\nnothing\n\njulia> result.response.usage\n{\n  \"input_tokens\": 25,\n  \"input_tokens_details\": {\n    \"image_tokens\": 0,\n    \"text_tokens\": 25\n  },\n  \"output_tokens_details\": {\n    \"image_tokens\": 1056,\n    \"text_tokens\": 446\n  },\n  \"total_tokens\": 1527,\n  \"output_tokens\": 1502\n}\n\njulia> save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot_julia.png\")\n\"robot_julia.png\"\n\nGenerated image:\n\n(Image: A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book)","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/embeddings/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> emb = Embeddings(\"Julia is a high-performance programming language for technical computing.\")\n\njulia> embeddingrequest!(emb)\n\njulia> emb.embeddings[1:5]  # first 5 dimensions\n5-element Vector{Float64}:\n  -0.039474\n  -0.009283\n  0.001706\n  -0.028087\n  0.063363\n\njulia> sqrt(sum(x^2 for x in emb.embeddings))  # L2 norm ≈ 1.0\n1.0","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/respond_basic/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> result = respond(\"Explain Julia's multiple dispatch in 2-3 sentences.\")\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Julia’s multiple dispatch means a function can have many method definitions, and Julia chooses which one to run based on the types of *all* arguments in a call (not just the first). This makes it easy to write generic code while still getting specialized, high-performance behavior for specific type combinations.\"\n\njulia> result.response.id\n\"resp_00e791c82448c27d006990c7a81de88194975ba388932de6b8\"\n\njulia> result.response.status\n\"completed\"\n\njulia> result.response.model\n\"gpt-5.2-2025-12-11\"\n\njulia> result.response.usage\n{\n  \"input_tokens\": 18,\n  \"input_tokens_details\": {\n    \"cached_tokens\": 0\n  },\n  \"output_tokens_details\": {\n    \"reasoning_tokens\": 0\n  },\n  \"total_tokens\": 81,\n  \"output_tokens\": 63\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#images_guide","page":"Image Generation","title":"Image Generation","text":"UniLM.jl supports image generation via the OpenAI Images API using models like gpt-image-1.5.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Basic-Usage","page":"Image Generation","title":"Basic Usage","text":"julia> result = generate_image(\n           \"A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book\",\n           size=\"1024x1024\",\n           quality=\"medium\"\n       )\n\njulia> result isa ImageSuccess\ntrue\n\njulia> length(image_data(result))\n1\n\njulia> length(image_data(result)[1])  # base64 string length\n2654660\n\njulia> save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot_julia.png\")\n\"robot_julia.png\"\n\n(Image: Generated image: A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#The-ImageGeneration-Type","page":"Image Generation","title":"The ImageGeneration Type","text":"For full control, construct an ImageGeneration object:\n\nusing UniLM\nusing JSON\n\nig = ImageGeneration(\n    prompt=\"A minimalist logo for a Julia programming package\",\n    model=\"gpt-image-1.5\",\n    size=\"1024x1024\",\n    quality=\"high\",\n    background=\"transparent\",\n    output_format=\"png\"\n)\nprintln(\"Model: \", ig.model)\nprintln(\"Size: \", ig.size)\nprintln(\"Quality: \", ig.quality)\nprintln(\"\\nRequest JSON:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(ig))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Configuration-Options","page":"Image Generation","title":"Configuration Options","text":"Parameter Values Default\nmodel \"gpt-image-1.5\" \"gpt-image-1.5\"\nsize \"1024x1024\", \"1536x1024\", \"1024x1536\", \"auto\" API default\nquality \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"auto\" API default\nbackground \"transparent\", \"opaque\", \"auto\" API default\noutput_format \"png\", \"webp\", \"jpeg\" API default\noutput_compression 0–100 (for webp/jpeg) API default\nn 1–10 1","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Multiple-Images","page":"Image Generation","title":"Multiple Images","text":"Generate multiple images in a single request:\n\nresult = generate_image(\"A cute robot learning to program\", n=3, size=\"1024x1024\")\n\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    imgs = image_data(result)\n    for (i, img) in enumerate(imgs)\n        save_image(img, \"robot_$i.png\")\n    end\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Transparent-Backgrounds","page":"Image Generation","title":"Transparent Backgrounds","text":"Perfect for logos and icons:\n\nresult = generate_image(\n    \"A simple geometric icon of a butterfly\",\n    background=\"transparent\",\n    output_format=\"png\",\n    quality=\"high\"\n)\n\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"butterfly_icon.png\")\n    # => PNG with transparent background\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Result-Structure","page":"Image Generation","title":"Result Structure","text":"# Show the type hierarchy for image results\nprintln(\"ImageSuccess <: \", supertype(ImageSuccess))\nprintln(\"ImageFailure <: \", supertype(ImageFailure))\nprintln(\"ImageCallError <: \", supertype(ImageCallError))\n\nresult = generate_image(\"A sunset over mountains\")\n\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    r = result.response\n\n    r.created                 # Unix timestamp\n    r.data                    # Vector{ImageObject}\n    r.data[1].b64_json        # base64-encoded image data\n    r.data[1].revised_prompt  # revised prompt (may be nothing)\n    r.usage                   # token usage Dict\n\n    # Convenience accessors\n    image_data(result)        # Vector{String} of base64 data\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"sunset.png\")\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Saving-Images","page":"Image Generation","title":"Saving Images","text":"The save_image helper decodes base64 and writes to disk:\n\n# Demonstrate save_image with a tiny test payload\ntmpfile = tempname() * \".txt\"\nUniLM.save_image(\"aGVsbG8=\", tmpfile)  # \"hello\" in base64\nprintln(\"File saved to: \", basename(tmpfile))\nprintln(\"Contents: \", read(tmpfile, String))\nrm(tmpfile)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#Error-Handling","page":"Image Generation","title":"Error Handling","text":"result = generate_image(\"A sunset over mountains\")\n\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"sunset.png\")\nelseif result isa ImageFailure\n    @warn \"HTTP $(result.status): $(result.response)\"\nelseif result isa ImageCallError\n    @error \"Call failed: $(result.error)\"\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/image_generation/#See-Also","page":"Image Generation","title":"See Also","text":"ImageGeneration — request configuration type\nImageResponse — response type\ngenerate_image — request function\nimage_data, save_image — accessor/utility functions","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_json_schema/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> schema = UniLM.json_schema(\"weather\", \"Weather data\", Dict(\n           \"type\" => \"object\",\n           \"properties\" => Dict(\n               \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\"),\n               \"temperature\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"number\"),\n               \"unit\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\"),\n               \"conditions\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n           ),\n           \"required\" => [\"location\", \"temperature\", \"unit\", \"conditions\"],\n           \"additionalProperties\" => false\n       ))\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", response_format=schema)\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"Respond with weather data in structured JSON.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What's the weather like in Tokyo?\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> JSON.parse(result.message.content)\n{\n  \"location\": \"Tokyo\",\n  \"temperature\": 22,\n  \"unit\": \"celsius\",\n  \"conditions\": \"Partly Cloudy\"\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#embeddings_api","page":"Embeddings","title":"Embeddings API","text":"Types and functions for the Embeddings API.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#Embeddings-Object","page":"Embeddings","title":"Embeddings Object","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#Construction","page":"Embeddings","title":"Construction","text":"using UniLM\n\n# Single input\nemb = Embeddings(\"Julia is a great language\")\nprintln(\"Model: \", emb.model)\nprintln(\"Embedding dims: \", length(emb.embeddings))\n\n# Batch input\nbatch = Embeddings([\"Hello\", \"World\", \"Julia\"])\nprintln(\"Batch size: \", length(batch.input))\nprintln(\"Each embedding dims: \", length(batch.embeddings[1]))","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#Request-Function","page":"Embeddings","title":"Request Function","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#Model-Constants","page":"Embeddings","title":"Model Constants","text":"println(\"Default embedding model: \", UniLM.GPTTextEmbedding3Small)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#Usage-Example","page":"Embeddings","title":"Usage Example","text":"julia> emb = Embeddings(\"Julia is a high-performance programming language for technical computing.\")\n\njulia> embeddingrequest!(emb)\n\njulia> emb.embeddings[1:5]  # first 5 dimensions\n5-element Vector{Float64}:\n  -0.039474\n  -0.009283\n  0.001706\n  -0.028087\n  0.063363\n\njulia> sqrt(sum(x^2 for x in emb.embeddings))  # L2 norm ≈ 1.0\n1.0","category":"section"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#UniLM.Embeddings","page":"Embeddings","title":"UniLM.Embeddings","text":"Embeddings(input::String)\nEmbeddings(input::Vector{String})\n\nCreate an embedding request for one or more text inputs. Uses the text-embedding-3-small model (1536-dimensional embeddings) by default.\n\nThe embeddings field is pre-allocated and filled in-place by embeddingrequest!.\n\nFields\n\nmodel::String: The embedding model name.\ninput::Union{String,Vector{String}}: Text(s) to embed.\nembeddings::Union{Vector{Float64},Vector{Vector{Float64}}}: Pre-allocated embedding vector(s).\nuser::Union{String,Nothing}: Optional end-user identifier.\n\nExample\n\nemb = Embeddings(\"Julia is a great language\")\nembeddingrequest!(emb)\nemb.embeddings  # => Float64[...] (1536 dims)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/embeddings/#UniLM.embeddingrequest!","page":"Embeddings","title":"UniLM.embeddingrequest!","text":"embeddingrequest!(emb::Embedding)\n\nSend a request to the OpenAI API to generate an embedding for the `input` in `emb`.\n\nResulting embedding is stored in the preallocated `embedding` field.  \n\n@kwdef struct Embedding\n    model::String = \"text-embedding-3-small\"\n    input::Union{String,Vector{String}}\n    embedding::Vector{Float64} = zeros(Float64, 1536)\n    user::Union{String,Nothing} = nothing\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#chat_guide","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Chat Completions","text":"The Chat Completions API is the classic way to interact with OpenAI's language models. UniLM.jl wraps it in a type-safe, stateful Chat object that tracks conversation history automatically.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Creating-a-Chat","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Creating a Chat","text":"using UniLM\nusing JSON\n\nchat = Chat(\n    model=\"gpt-5.2\",        # model name\n    temperature=0.7,        # sampling temperature\n    max_tokens=1000,        # response length limit\n)\nprintln(\"Model: \", chat.model)\nprintln(\"Messages: \", length(chat))\n\nAll parameters are optional with sensible defaults. See Chat for the full list.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Building-Conversations","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Building Conversations","text":"Messages are added with push!. UniLM.jl enforces conversation structure at the type level — you cannot create invalid message sequences:\n\n# System message must come first\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a helpful Julia programming tutor.\"))\n\n# Then user messages\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What are parametric types?\"))\n\nprintln(\"Conversation length: \", length(chat))\nprintln(\"First message role: \", chat[1].role)\nprintln(\"Last message role: \", chat[end].role)\n\nThe convenience Val(:system) and Val(:user) constructors keep things concise. You can also use the keyword constructor:\n\nchat2 = Chat()\npush!(chat2, Message(role=\"system\", content=\"Be helpful\"))\npush!(chat2, Message(role=\"user\", content=\"Tell me more\"))\nprintln(\"chat2 length: \", length(chat2))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Conversation-Rules","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Conversation Rules","text":"The first message must have role system\nMessages must alternate roles (no two consecutive messages from the same role)\nAt least content, tool_calls, or refusal_message must be non-nothing\nAttempting to violate these rules logs a warning and the message is not added\n\n# Demonstrate validation\nchat3 = Chat()\npush!(chat3, Message(Val(:system), \"sys\"))\npush!(chat3, Message(Val(:user), \"hello\"))\npush!(chat3, Message(Val(:user), \"hello again\"))  # rejected — same role\nprintln(\"Length after duplicate push: \", length(chat3), \" (second user msg rejected)\")","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Sending-Requests","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Sending Requests","text":"result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\nThe ! suffix is a Julia convention — chatrequest! mutates chat by appending the assistant's response to the message history (when history=true).","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Result-Handling","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Result Handling","text":"julia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"Multiple dispatch is a feature in programming languages, including Julia, that allows the selection of a method to execute based on the types of all its arguments, rather than just the first one. This enables more flexible and expressive code, as it can define different behaviors for a function depending on the combination of argument types. It supports polymorphism, making it easier to write generic code that works with multiple types.\"\n\njulia> result.message.finish_reason\n\"stop\"\n\njulia> length(chat)  # system + user + assistant\n3","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#One-Shot-Requests-via-Keywords","page":"Chat Completions","title":"One-Shot Requests via Keywords","text":"Skip the Chat object entirely for simple one-off requests:\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(\n           systemprompt=\"You are a calculator. Respond only with the number.\",\n           userprompt=\"What is 42 * 17?\",\n           model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n           temperature=0.0\n       )\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"714\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Multi-Turn-Conversations","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Multi-Turn Conversations","text":"Because chatrequest! appends the response, you can keep chatting:\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\")\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a concise Julia programming tutor.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What is multiple dispatch? Answer in 2-3 sentences.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"Multiple dispatch is a feature in programming languages, including Julia, that allows the selection of a method to execute based on the types of all its arguments, rather than just the first one. This enables more flexible and expressive code, as it can define different behaviors for a function depending on the combination of argument types. It supports polymorphism, making it easier to write generic code that works with multiple types.\"\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Give a short Julia code example of it.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> println(result.message.content)\n# (multi-line code example output)\n\njulia> length(chat)  # system + user + assistant + user + assistant\n5","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Checking-Conversation-Validity","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Checking Conversation Validity","text":"println(\"Is chat valid? \", issendvalid(chat))  # true — system + user\n\nempty_chat = Chat()\nprintln(\"Is empty chat valid? \", issendvalid(empty_chat))  # false\n\nThis checks:\n\nAt least 2 messages\nFirst message is system\nLast message is user\nNo consecutive same-role messages","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Models","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Models","text":"UniLM.jl works with any model name string. Common choices:\n\nModel Usage\n\"gpt-5.2\" Best quality (default)\n\"gpt-4o-mini\" Fast and cheap\n\"gpt-4.1-mini\" Balanced performance\n\"o3\" Extended reasoning\n\"o4-mini\" Fast reasoning","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#JSON-Serialization","page":"Chat Completions","title":"JSON Serialization","text":"The Chat object serializes cleanly to JSON for the API:\n\nprintln(JSON.json(chat))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#Retry-Behaviour","page":"Chat Completions","title":"Retry Behaviour","text":"chatrequest! automatically retries on HTTP 500/503 errors with a 1-second delay, up to 30 retries. This is transparent and requires no configuration.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/chat_completions/#See-Also","page":"Chat Completions","title":"See Also","text":"Chat — full type reference\nMessage — message type reference\nTool Calling — function calling with Chat Completions\nStreaming — real-time streaming\nStructured Output — JSON-constrained generation","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#tools_guide","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Tool Calling","text":"Both the Chat Completions and Responses APIs support function/tool calling — the model can decide to invoke functions you define, and you return the results.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Chat-Completions-Tool-Calling","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Chat Completions Tool Calling","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Defining-Tools","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Defining Tools","text":"Wrap your function schema in a GPTTool:\n\nusing UniLM\nusing JSON\n\nweather_tool = GPTTool(\n    func=GPTFunctionSignature(\n        name=\"get_weather\",\n        description=\"Get current weather for a location\",\n        parameters=Dict(\n            \"type\" => \"object\",\n            \"properties\" => Dict(\n                \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"description\" => \"City name\"),\n                \"unit\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"enum\" => [\"celsius\", \"fahrenheit\"])\n            ),\n            \"required\" => [\"location\"]\n        )\n    )\n)\nprintln(\"Tool type: \", weather_tool.type)\nprintln(\"Function name: \", weather_tool.func.name)\nprintln(\"Tool JSON:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(JSON.lower(weather_tool)))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Making-Tool-Enabled-Requests","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Making Tool-Enabled Requests","text":"chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-5.2\", tools=[weather_tool])\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a helpful assistant with access to weather data.\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What's the weather in Paris?\"))\nprintln(\"Chat has \", length(chat.tools), \" tool(s) registered\")\nprintln(\"Request body:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(chat))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Handling-Tool-Calls","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Handling Tool Calls","text":"When the model wants to call a function, the result message will have finish_reason == \"tool_calls\":\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.finish_reason\n\"tool_calls\"\n\njulia> tc = result.message.tool_calls[1]\n\njulia> tc.func.name\n\"get_weather\"\n\njulia> tc.func.arguments\n{\n  \"location\": \"Paris\"\n}\n\n# You can then execute your function and send the result back:\n# push!(chat.messages, Message(role=\"tool\", content=my_get_weather(\"Paris\"), tool_call_id=tc.id))\n# final = chatrequest!(chat)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Controlling-Tool-Choice","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Controlling Tool Choice","text":"# Let the model decide\nchat = Chat(tools=[weather_tool], tool_choice=\"auto\")\n\n# Force the model to use a tool\nchat = Chat(tools=[weather_tool], tool_choice=\"required\")\n\n# Prevent tool use\nchat = Chat(tools=[weather_tool], tool_choice=\"none\")","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Responses-API-Tool-Calling","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Responses API Tool Calling","text":"The Responses API makes tool calling more ergonomic with dedicated types.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Function-Tools","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Function Tools","text":"tool = function_tool(\n    \"calculate\",\n    \"Evaluate a math expression\",\n    parameters=Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"expression\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"expression\"]\n    ),\n    strict=true\n)\nprintln(\"Tool: \", tool.name, \" (strict=\", tool.strict, \")\")\nprintln(\"JSON: \", JSON.json(JSON.lower(tool)))\n\njulia> result = respond(\"What's the weather in Tokyo? Use celsius.\", tools=[weather_tool])\n\njulia> calls = function_calls(result)\n\njulia> calls[1][\"name\"]\n\"get_weather\"\n\njulia> JSON.parse(calls[1][\"arguments\"])\n{\n  \"location\": \"Tokyo\",\n  \"unit\": \"celsius\"\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Web-Search","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Web Search","text":"The model can search the web — no function implementation needed:\n\nws = web_search(context_size=\"high\")\nprintln(\"Web search tool type: \", typeof(ws))\nprintln(\"Context size: \", ws.search_context_size)\n\njulia> result = respond(\n           \"What is the latest stable release of the Julia programming language?\",\n           tools=[web_search()]\n       )\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"The latest **stable** release of the Julia programming language is **Julia v1.12.5**.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#File-Search","page":"Tool Calling","title":"File Search","text":"Search over your uploaded vector stores:\n\nresult = respond(\n    \"Find the error handling policy\",\n    tools=[file_search([\"vs_store_id_123\"], max_results=5)]\n)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#Combining-Tools","page":"Tool Calling","title":"Combining Tools","text":"Mix different tool types freely:\n\ntools = [\n    web_search(),\n    function_tool(\"save_summary\", \"Save a summary to the database\",\n        parameters=Dict(\n            \"type\" => \"object\",\n            \"properties\" => Dict(\n                \"title\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\"),\n                \"content\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n            )\n        )\n    )\n]\nprintln(\"Number of tools: \", length(tools))\nfor t in tools\n    println(\"  - \", typeof(t))\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tool_calling/#See-Also","page":"Tool Calling","title":"See Also","text":"GPTTool, GPTFunctionSignature — Chat Completions tool types\nFunctionTool, WebSearchTool, FileSearchTool — Responses API tool types\nfunction_tool, web_search, file_search — convenience constructors","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Image-Generation-API","page":"Images","title":"Image Generation API","text":"Types and functions for the Image Generation API (/v1/images/generations).","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Request-Type","page":"Images","title":"Request Type","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Construction","page":"Images","title":"Construction","text":"using UniLM\nusing JSON\n\n# Minimal request\nig = ImageGeneration(prompt=\"A watercolor painting of a sunset\")\nprintln(\"Model: \", ig.model)\nprintln(\"Prompt: \", ig.prompt)\n\n# Full options\nig2 = ImageGeneration(\n    prompt=\"A minimalist logo for a Julia package\",\n    size=\"1024x1024\",\n    quality=\"high\",\n    background=\"transparent\",\n    output_format=\"png\",\n    n=2\n)\nprintln(\"\\nFull options:\")\nprintln(\"  Size: \", ig2.size)\nprintln(\"  Quality: \", ig2.quality)\nprintln(\"  Background: \", ig2.background)\nprintln(\"  Format: \", ig2.output_format)\nprintln(\"  Count: \", ig2.n)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#JSON-Serialization","page":"Images","title":"JSON Serialization","text":"ig = ImageGeneration(prompt=\"A cute robot\", quality=\"high\", size=\"1024x1024\")\nprintln(JSON.json(ig))","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Response-Types","page":"Images","title":"Response Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Result-Types","page":"Images","title":"Result Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Request-Function","page":"Images","title":"Request Function","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Usage-Examples","page":"Images","title":"Usage Examples","text":"julia> result = generate_image(\n           \"A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book\",\n           size=\"1024x1024\", quality=\"medium\"\n       )\n\njulia> result isa ImageSuccess\ntrue\n\njulia> length(image_data(result))\n1\n\njulia> save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot_julia.png\")\n\"robot_julia.png\"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Accessor-Functions","page":"Images","title":"Accessor Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Saving-Images","page":"Images","title":"Saving Images","text":"result = generate_image(\"A sunset over mountains\", n=3)\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    for (i, img) in enumerate(image_data(result))\n        save_image(img, \"sunset_$i.png\")\n    end\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#Parameters-Reference","page":"Images","title":"Parameters Reference","text":"Parameter Type Default Description\nmodel String \"gpt-image-1.5\" Image generation model\nprompt String (required) Text description of the image\nn Int 1 Number of images (1–10)\nsize String \"auto\" \"1024x1024\", \"1536x1024\", etc.\nquality String \"auto\" \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\"\nbackground String \"auto\" \"transparent\", \"opaque\"\noutput_format String \"png\" \"png\", \"webp\", \"jpeg\"\noutput_compression Int — 0–100, for webp/jpeg\nuser String — End-user identifier","category":"section"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.ImageGeneration","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.ImageGeneration","text":"ImageGeneration(; prompt, model=\"gpt-image-1.5\", kwargs...)\n\nConfiguration struct for an OpenAI Image Generation API request.\n\nKey Fields\n\nmodel::String: Model to use (default: \"gpt-image-1.5\")\nprompt::String: A text description of the desired image\nn::Union{Int,Nothing}: Number of images to generate (1–10)\nsize::Union{String,Nothing}: Size (\"1024x1024\", \"1536x1024\", \"1024x1536\", \"auto\")\nquality::Union{String,Nothing}: Quality level (\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"auto\")\nbackground::Union{String,Nothing}: Background (\"transparent\", \"opaque\", \"auto\")\noutput_format::Union{String,Nothing}: File format (\"png\", \"webp\", \"jpeg\")\noutput_compression::Union{Int,Nothing}: Compression (0–100, for \"webp\" and \"jpeg\")\nuser::Union{String,Nothing}: End-user identifier\n\nExamples\n\n# Simple prompt\nImageGeneration(prompt=\"A watercolor painting of a mountain sunset\")\n\n# With all options\nImageGeneration(\n    prompt=\"A minimalist logo for a Julia package\",\n    size=\"1024x1024\",\n    quality=\"high\",\n    background=\"transparent\",\n    output_format=\"png\"\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.ImageObject","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.ImageObject","text":"ImageObject\n\nA single generated image from the API response.\n\nFields\n\nb64_json::Union{String,Nothing}: Base64-encoded image data\nrevised_prompt::Union{String,Nothing}: The prompt as revised by the model\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.ImageResponse","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.ImageResponse","text":"ImageResponse\n\nParsed response from the Image Generation API.\n\nAccessors\n\nimage_data(r) — extract base64-encoded image data\nr.created, r.data, r.usage — basic fields\nr.raw — the complete raw JSON dict\n\nFields\n\ncreated::Int64: Timestamp when the response was created\ndata::Vector{ImageObject}: Generated images\nusage::Union{Dict{String,Any},Nothing}: Token usage information\nraw::Dict{String,Any}: Complete raw JSON response\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.ImageSuccess","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.ImageSuccess","text":"ImageSuccess <: LLMRequestResponse\n\nSuccessful image generation. Access the parsed response via .response.\n\nExamples\n\nresult = generate_image(\"A cute robot\")\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    imgs = image_data(result)   # Vector{String} of base64 images\n    save_image(imgs[1], \"robot.png\")\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.ImageFailure","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.ImageFailure","text":"ImageFailure <: LLMRequestResponse\n\nHTTP-level failure from the Image Generation API. Contains the response body and status code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.ImageCallError","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.ImageCallError","text":"ImageCallError <: LLMRequestResponse\n\nException-level error during an Image Generation API call (network, parsing, etc.).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.generate_image","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.generate_image","text":"generate_image(ig::ImageGeneration; retries=0)\n\nSend a request to the OpenAI Image Generation API.\n\nReturns ImageSuccess, ImageFailure, or ImageCallError.\n\nExamples\n\nig = ImageGeneration(prompt=\"A cute robot learning Julia\", quality=\"high\")\nresult = generate_image(ig)\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    println(\"Generated $(length(result.response.data)) image(s)\")\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot.png\")\nend\n\n\n\n\n\ngenerate_image(prompt::String; kwargs...)\n\nConvenience method: create an ImageGeneration from a prompt + keyword arguments and send it.\n\nExamples\n\n# Simple generation\nresult = generate_image(\"A watercolor painting of a Julia butterfly\")\n\n# With options\nresult = generate_image(\n    \"A minimalist logo\",\n    size=\"1024x1024\",\n    quality=\"high\",\n    background=\"transparent\"\n)\n\n# Save to file\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"logo.png\")\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.image_data","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.image_data","text":"image_data(r::ImageResponse)::Vector{String}\nimage_data(r::ImageSuccess)::Vector{String}\n\nExtract base64-encoded image data from a response. Returns a vector of base64 strings, one per generated image.\n\nExamples\n\nresult = generate_image(\"A sunset over mountains\")\nimgs = image_data(result)       # Vector{String}\nlength(imgs)                     # number of images generated\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/images/#UniLM.save_image","page":"Images","title":"UniLM.save_image","text":"save_image(img_b64::String, filepath::String)\n\nDecode a base64-encoded image and save it to a file.\n\nExamples\n\nresult = generate_image(\"A watercolor landscape\")\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"landscape.png\")\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#Embeddings","page":"Embeddings","title":"Embeddings","text":"UniLM.jl supports text embeddings via the OpenAI Embeddings API using the text-embedding-3-small model (1536 dimensions) by default.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#Basic-Usage","page":"Embeddings","title":"Basic Usage","text":"using UniLM\n\n# Single text\nemb = Embeddings(\"Julia is a high-performance programming language\")\nprintln(\"Model: \", emb.model)\nprintln(\"Embedding dimensions: \", length(emb.embeddings))\nprintln(\"Pre-allocated (all zeros): \", all(x -> x == 0.0, emb.embeddings))\n\nAfter calling the API, the embeddings are filled in-place:\n\njulia> emb = Embeddings(\"Julia is a high-performance programming language for technical computing.\")\n\njulia> embeddingrequest!(emb)\n\njulia> emb.embeddings[1:5]  # first 5 dimensions\n5-element Vector{Float64}:\n  -0.039474\n  -0.009283\n  0.001706\n  -0.028087\n  0.063363\n\njulia> sqrt(sum(x^2 for x in emb.embeddings))  # L2 norm ≈ 1.0\n1.0","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#Batch-Embeddings","page":"Embeddings","title":"Batch Embeddings","text":"Embed multiple texts in a single API call:\n\ntexts = [\n    \"Julia is fast\",\n    \"Python is popular\",\n    \"Rust is safe\"\n]\n\nemb = Embeddings(texts)\nprintln(\"Model: \", emb.model)\nprintln(\"Number of texts: \", length(emb.input))\nprintln(\"Embeddings per text: \", length(emb.embeddings[1]), \" dimensions\")\n\nembeddingrequest!(emb)\n\n# Each embedding is a 1536-dimensional Float64 vector\nlength(emb.embeddings[1])  # 1536\nlength(emb.embeddings[2])  # 1536","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#Computing-Similarity","page":"Embeddings","title":"Computing Similarity","text":"A common use case is computing cosine similarity between embeddings:\n\nusing LinearAlgebra\n\nemb = Embeddings([\"Julia\", \"Python\", \"Rust\", \"Fortran\"])\nembeddingrequest!(emb)\n\n# Cosine similarity between embeddings\nsim = dot(emb.embeddings[1], emb.embeddings[4]) /\n      (norm(emb.embeddings[1]) * norm(emb.embeddings[4]))\n# Similarity score between 0 and 1","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#Available-Models","page":"Embeddings","title":"Available Models","text":"Model Dimensions Notes\ntext-embedding-3-small 1536 Default, good balance\ntext-embedding-3-large 3072 Higher quality, more dimensions\n\nnote: Note\nThe default Embeddings constructor pre-allocates for 1536 dimensions (text-embedding-3-small). To use text-embedding-3-large, you would need to adjust the embedding vector size accordingly.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#In-Place-Design","page":"Embeddings","title":"In-Place Design","text":"The Embeddings struct pre-allocates the embedding vectors at construction time. embeddingrequest! fills them in-place — no allocation on the hot path. This is idiomatic Julia for performance-sensitive workloads.\n\nemb = Embeddings(\"test\")\nprintln(\"Pre-allocated length: \", length(emb.embeddings))\nprintln(\"All zeros before API call: \", all(x -> x == 0.0, emb.embeddings))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/embeddings/#API-Reference","page":"Embeddings","title":"API Reference","text":"See the Embeddings API page for full type documentation.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#structured_guide","page":"Structured Output","title":"Structured Output","text":"Force the model to produce valid JSON conforming to a schema. Both APIs support this.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#Chat-Completions","page":"Structured Output","title":"Chat Completions","text":"Use ResponseFormat to control the output format:","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#Free-Form-JSON","page":"Structured Output","title":"Free-Form JSON","text":"using UniLM\nusing JSON\n\nchat = Chat(\n    model=\"gpt-5.2\",\n    response_format=ResponseFormat()  # type=\"json_object\"\n)\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You output JSON. Always respond with valid JSON.\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"List 3 programming languages with their year of creation.\"))\nprintln(\"Response format type: \", chat.response_format.type)\nprintln(\"Request body:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(chat))\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", response_format=ResponseFormat())\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You always respond in valid JSON.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"List 3 programming languages with their year of creation.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> JSON.parse(result.message.content)\n{\n  \"languages\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Python\",\n      \"year\": 1991\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Java\",\n      \"year\": 1995\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n      \"year\": 1995\n    }\n  ]\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#JSON-Schema-(Strict)","page":"Structured Output","title":"JSON Schema (Strict)","text":"schema = ResponseFormat(UniLM.JsonSchemaAPI(\n    name=\"languages\",\n    description=\"A list of programming languages\",\n    schema=Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"languages\" => Dict(\n                \"type\" => \"array\",\n                \"items\" => Dict(\n                    \"type\" => \"object\",\n                    \"properties\" => Dict(\n                        \"name\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\"),\n                        \"year\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"integer\")\n                    ),\n                    \"required\" => [\"name\", \"year\"]\n                )\n            )\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"languages\"]\n    )\n))\n\nchat = Chat(model=\"gpt-5.2\", response_format=schema)\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"Return structured data about programming languages.\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"List Julia, Python, and Rust\"))\nprintln(\"Schema name: \", schema.json_schema.name)\nprintln(\"Response format type: \", schema.type)\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> data = JSON.parse(result.message.content)\n# result.message.content is guaranteed to match the schema","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#Responses-API","page":"Structured Output","title":"Responses API","text":"The Responses API uses TextConfig with convenience constructors:","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#JSON-Object","page":"Structured Output","title":"JSON Object","text":"julia> result = respond(\"List 3 colors as a JSON object\", text=json_object_format())\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n# Returns valid JSON conforming to \"json_object\" format","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#JSON-Schema","page":"Structured Output","title":"JSON Schema","text":"fmt = json_schema_format(\n    \"colors\",\n    \"A structured list of colors\",\n    Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"colors\" => Dict(\n                \"type\" => \"array\",\n                \"items\" => Dict(\n                    \"type\" => \"object\",\n                    \"properties\" => Dict(\n                        \"name\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\"),\n                        \"hex\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n                    ),\n                    \"required\" => [\"name\", \"hex\"]\n                )\n            )\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"colors\"]\n    ),\n    strict=true\n)\nprintln(\"Format type: \", fmt.format.type)\nprintln(\"Schema strict: \", fmt.format.strict)\n\njulia> result = respond(\"List red, green, and blue with their hex codes\", text=fmt)\n\njulia> JSON.parse(output_text(result))\n# Returns JSON matching the defined schema","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#Plain-Text-Format","page":"Structured Output","title":"Plain Text Format","text":"tc = text_format()\nprintln(\"Default format type: \", tc.format.type)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#Convenience-Constructors","page":"Structured Output","title":"Convenience Constructors","text":"Constructor Format\njson_object_format() Unstructured JSON\njson_schema_format(name, desc, schema) Schema-constrained JSON\ntext_format() Plain text (default)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/structured_output/#See-Also","page":"Structured Output","title":"See Also","text":"ResponseFormat — Chat Completions format type\nTextConfig, TextFormatSpec — Responses API format types","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#backend_guide","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"Multi-Backend Support","text":"UniLM.jl supports multiple LLM service backends through the ServiceEndpoint type hierarchy. Switching backends requires only changing the service parameter.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#Available-Backends","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"Available Backends","text":"Backend Type Env Variables\nOpenAI (default) OPENAIServiceEndpoint OPENAI_API_KEY\nAzure OpenAI AZUREServiceEndpoint AZURE_OPENAI_BASE_URL, AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY, AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION\nGoogle Gemini GEMINIServiceEndpoint GEMINI_API_KEY","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#OpenAI-(Default)","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"OpenAI (Default)","text":"using UniLM\nusing JSON\n\n# OpenAI is the default — no need to specify service\nchat = Chat(model=\"gpt-5.2\")\nprintln(\"Service: \", chat.service)\nprintln(\"Model: \", chat.model)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#Azure-OpenAI","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"Azure OpenAI","text":"# Set environment variables\nENV[\"AZURE_OPENAI_BASE_URL\"] = \"https://your-resource.openai.azure.com\"\nENV[\"AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY\"] = \"your-key\"\nENV[\"AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION\"] = \"2024-02-01\"\nENV[\"AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOY_NAME_GPT_5_2\"] = \"your-gpt52-deployment\"\n\n# Use Azure\nchat = Chat(service=AZUREServiceEndpoint, model=\"gpt-5.2\")\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"Hello from Azure!\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Hi!\"))\nresult = chatrequest!(chat)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#Custom-Deployment-Names","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"Custom Deployment Names","text":"If your Azure deployment has a custom name:\n\nUniLM.add_azure_deploy_name!(\"my-custom-model\", \"my-deployment-name\")\nprintln(\"Registered deployments: \", collect(keys(UniLM._MODEL_ENDPOINTS_AZURE_OPENAI)))\ndelete!(UniLM._MODEL_ENDPOINTS_AZURE_OPENAI, \"my-custom-model\")  # cleanup","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#Google-Gemini","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"Google Gemini","text":"ENV[\"GEMINI_API_KEY\"] = \"your-gemini-key\"\n\nchat = Chat(service=GEMINIServiceEndpoint, model=\"gemini-2.5-flash\")\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a helpful assistant.\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Hello!\"))\nresult = chatrequest!(chat)\n\nAvailable Gemini models:\n\n\"gemini-2.5-flash\"\n\"gemini-2.5-pro\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#Responses-API-Backend","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"Responses API Backend","text":"The Responses API also supports the service parameter:\n\nr = Respond(\n    service=UniLM.OPENAIServiceEndpoint,\n    model=\"gpt-5.2\",\n    input=\"Hello!\",\n)\nprintln(\"Service: \", r.service)\nprintln(\"Model: \", r.model)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/multi_backend/#See-Also","page":"Multi-Backend","title":"See Also","text":"ServiceEndpoint — backend type hierarchy\nOPENAIServiceEndpoint, AZUREServiceEndpoint, GEMINIServiceEndpoint — specific backends","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#chat_api","page":"Chat Types","title":"Chat Completions API","text":"Types and functions for the Chat Completions API.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Chat-Object","page":"Chat Types","title":"Chat Object","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Messages","page":"Chat Types","title":"Messages","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Convenience-Constructors","page":"Chat Types","title":"Convenience Constructors","text":"using UniLM\n\nsys = Message(Val(:system), \"You are a helpful assistant\")\nusr = Message(Val(:user), \"Hello!\")\nprintln(\"System role: \", sys.role)\nprintln(\"User role: \", usr.role)\nprintln(\"User content: \", usr.content)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Conversation-Management","page":"Chat Types","title":"Conversation Management","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Building-a-Conversation","page":"Chat Types","title":"Building a Conversation","text":"chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-5.2\")\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a helpful assistant\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What is Julia?\"))\nprintln(\"Messages: \", length(chat))\nprintln(\"Valid for sending: \", issendvalid(chat))","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Tools","page":"Chat Types","title":"Tools","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Output-Format","page":"Chat Types","title":"Output Format","text":"using JSON\n\n# JSON object format\nfmt = ResponseFormat()\nprintln(\"Type: \", fmt.type)\nprintln(\"JSON: \", JSON.json(fmt))","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Request-Function","page":"Chat Types","title":"Request Function","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Role-Constants","page":"Chat Types","title":"Role Constants","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#Model-Constants","page":"Chat Types","title":"Model Constants","text":"println(\"GPT5_2: \", UniLM.GPT5_2)\nprintln(\"GPT5_2Mini: \", UniLM.GPT5_2Mini)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.Chat","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.Chat","text":"chat = Chat()\n\nCreates a new Chat object with default settings:\n\nmodel is set to gpt-5.2\nmessages is set to an empty Vector{Message}\nhistory is set to true\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.Message","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.Message","text":"Message(; role, content=nothing, name=nothing, finish_reason=nothing, refusal_message=nothing, tool_calls=nothing, tool_call_id=nothing)\n\nRepresents a single message in a Chat Completions conversation.\n\nFields\n\nrole::String: One of RoleSystem, RoleUser, RoleAssistant, or RoleTool.\ncontent::Union{String,Nothing}: The text content of the message.\nname::Union{String,Nothing}: Optional name for the participant.\nfinish_reason::Union{String,Nothing}: Why the model stopped generating (e.g. \"stop\", \"tool_calls\").\nrefusal_message::Union{String,Nothing}: Refusal text when content is filtered.\ntool_calls::Union{Nothing,Vector{GPTToolCall}}: Tool calls requested by the assistant.\ntool_call_id::Union{String,Nothing}: Required when role is \"tool\" — the ID of the tool call being responded to.\n\nValidation\n\nAt least one of content, tool_calls, or refusal_message must be non-nothing.\ntool_call_id is required when role == \"tool\".\n\nConvenience Constructors\n\nMessage(Val(:system), \"You are a helpful assistant\")\nMessage(Val(:user), \"Hello!\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.issendvalid","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.issendvalid","text":"is_send_valid(chat::Chat)::Bool\n\nCheck if the conversation is valid for sending to the API.\n\nThis check employs a rough heuristic that works for practical purposes. \n        \nIt checks if the conversation has at least two messages, the first message is from the system, the last message is from the user, and there are no consecutive messages from the same role. However, this is not a foolproof check and may not work in all cases (e.g. imagine that you passed another system message in the middle of the conversation).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.update!","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.update!","text":"update!(chat::Chat, msg::Message)\n\nUpdate the chat with a new message.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.GPTTool","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.GPTTool","text":"GPTTool(; type=\"function\", func)\n\nWraps a GPTFunctionSignature for use in the tools parameter of a Chat.\n\nExample\n\ntool = GPTTool(func=GPTFunctionSignature(\n    name=\"get_weather\",\n    description=\"Get the current weather\",\n    parameters=Dict(\"type\" => \"object\", \"properties\" => Dict())\n))\nchat = Chat(tools=[tool])\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.GPTFunctionSignature","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.GPTFunctionSignature","text":"GPTFunctionSignature(; name, description=nothing, parameters=nothing)\n\nDescribes a function that can be called by the model in the Chat Completions API.\n\nFields\n\nname::String: The name of the function.\ndescription::Union{String,Nothing}: A description of what the function does.\nparameters::Union{AbstractDict,Nothing}: JSON Schema object describing the function parameters.\n\nExample\n\nsig = GPTFunctionSignature(\n    name=\"get_weather\",\n    description=\"Get the current weather in a given location\",\n    parameters=Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"description\" => \"The city\")\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"location\"]\n    )\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.GPTToolCall","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.GPTToolCall","text":"GPTToolCall(; id, type=\"function\", func)\n\nRepresents a tool call returned by the model. Contains the call id (used to match results back), the tool type, and the [GPTFunction] with name and parsed arguments.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.GPTFunctionCallResult","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.GPTFunctionCallResult","text":"GPTFunctionCallResult{T}\n\nHolds the result of executing a function that was requested by the model via a tool call.\n\nFields\n\nname::Union{String,Symbol}: The function name.\norigincall::GPTFunction: The original [GPTFunction] call from the model.\nresult::T: The result of executing the function.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.ResponseFormat","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.ResponseFormat","text":"ResponseFormat(; type=\"json_object\", json_schema=nothing)\nResponseFormat(json_schema)\n\nSpecifies the output format for Chat Completions.\n\nFields\n\ntype::String: \"json_object\" or \"json_schema\".\njson_schema::Union{JsonSchemaAPI,AbstractDict,Nothing}: Schema definition when type is \"json_schema\".\n\nExamples\n\n# Free-form JSON\nfmt = ResponseFormat()\n\n# Structured JSON via schema\nfmt = ResponseFormat(JsonSchemaAPI(\n    name=\"result\",\n    description=\"A structured result\",\n    schema=Dict(\"type\" => \"object\", \"properties\" => Dict())\n))\n\nnote: Note\nUse the convenience constructors json_object() and json_schema() for cleaner code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.chatrequest!","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.chatrequest!","text":"chatrequest!(chat::Chat, retries=0, callback=nothing)\n\nSend a request to the OpenAI API to generate a response to the messages in conv.\n\nThe callback function is called for each chunk of the response. The close Ref is also passed to the callback function, which can be used to close the stream (for example when not satisfied with the intermediate results and want to stop the stream).\n\nThe signature of the callback function is:\n    `callback(chunk::Union{String, Message}, close::Ref{Bool})`\n\n\n\n\n\nFlexible keyword arguments usage\n\nchatrequest!(; kwargs...) Send a request to the OpenAI API to generate a response to the messages in conv.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nservice::Type{<:ServiceEndpoint} = AZUREServiceEndpoint: The service endpoint to use (e.g., AZUREServiceEndpoint, OPENAIServiceEndpoint).\nmodel::String = \"gpt-5.2\": The model to use for the chat completion.\nsystemprompt::Union{Message,String}: The system prompt message.\nuserprompt::Union{Message,String}: The user prompt message.\nmessages::Conversation = Message[]: The conversation history or the system/prompt messages.\nhistory::Bool = true: Whether to include the conversation history in the request.\ntools::Union{Vector{GPTTool},Nothing} = nothing: A list of tools the model may call.\ntool_choice::Union{String,GPTToolChoice,Nothing} = nothing: Controls which (if any) function is called by the model. e.g. \"auto\", \"none\", GPTToolChoice.\nparallel_tool_calls::Union{Bool,Nothing} = false: Whether to enable parallel function calling.\ntemperature::Union{Float64,Nothing} = nothing: Sampling temperature (0.0-2.0). Higher values make output more random. Mutually exclusive with top_p.\ntop_p::Union{Float64,Nothing} = nothing: Nucleus sampling parameter (0.0-1.0). Mutually exclusive with temperature.\nn::Union{Int64,Nothing} = nothing: How many chat completion choices to generate for each input message (1-10).\nstream::Union{Bool,Nothing} = nothing: If set, partial message deltas will be sent, like in ChatGPT.\nstop::Union{Vector{String},String,Nothing} = nothing: Up to 4 sequences where the API will stop generating further tokens.\nmax_tokens::Union{Int64,Nothing} = nothing: The maximum number of tokens to generate in the chat completion.\npresence_penalty::Union{Float64,Nothing} = nothing: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far.\nresponse_format::Union{ResponseFormat,Nothing} = nothing: An object specifying the format that the model must output. e.g., ResponseFormat(type=\"json_object\").\nfrequency_penalty::Union{Float64,Nothing} = nothing: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far.\nlogit_bias::Union{AbstractDict{String,Float64},Nothing} = nothing: Modify the likelihood of specified tokens appearing in the completion.\nuser::Union{String,Nothing} = nothing: A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse.\nseed::Union{Int64,Nothing} = nothing: This feature is in Beta. If specified, the system will make a best effort to sample deterministically.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.RoleSystem","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.RoleSystem","text":"RoleSystem\n\nRole constant \"system\" — used for system-level instructions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.RoleUser","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.RoleUser","text":"RoleUser\n\nRole constant \"user\" — used for user messages.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"api/chat/#UniLM.RoleAssistant","page":"Chat Types","title":"UniLM.RoleAssistant","text":"RoleAssistant\n\nRole constant \"assistant\" — used for model-generated messages.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"_generated/chat_function_call/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> sig = GPTFunctionSignature(\n           name=\"get_weather\",\n           description=\"Get the current weather for a location\",\n           parameters=Dict(\n               \"type\" => \"object\",\n               \"properties\" => Dict(\n                   \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"description\" => \"City name\"),\n                   \"unit\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"enum\" => [\"celsius\", \"fahrenheit\"])\n               ),\n               \"required\" => [\"location\"]\n           )\n       )\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", tools=[GPTTool(func=sig)])\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"Always use the provided tools to answer.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What is the weather in Paris?\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.finish_reason\n\"tool_calls\"\n\njulia> tc = result.message.tool_calls[1]\n\njulia> tc.func.name\n\"get_weather\"\n\njulia> tc.func.arguments\n{\n  \"location\": \"Paris\"\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Responses-API","page":"Responses Types","title":"Responses API","text":"Types and functions for the Responses API — the newer, more flexible alternative to Chat Completions.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Request-Type","page":"Responses Types","title":"Request Type","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Construction","page":"Responses Types","title":"Construction","text":"using UniLM\nusing JSON\n\n# Simple text request\nr = Respond(input=\"Tell me a joke\")\nprintln(\"Model: \", r.model)\nprintln(\"Input: \", r.input)\n\n# With instructions and tools\nr2 = Respond(\n    input=\"What's the weather in Paris?\",\n    instructions=\"You are a helpful weather assistant\",\n    tools=[web_search()]\n)\nprintln(\"Has instructions: \", !isnothing(r2.instructions))\nprintln(\"Tools: \", length(r2.tools))","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Response-Object","page":"Responses Types","title":"Response Object","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Result-Types","page":"Responses Types","title":"Result Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Accessor-Functions","page":"Responses Types","title":"Accessor Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Request-Functions","page":"Responses Types","title":"Request Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Input-Helpers","page":"Responses Types","title":"Input Helpers","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Multimodal-Input","page":"Responses Types","title":"Multimodal Input","text":"# Text-only input\nmsg = InputMessage(role=\"user\", content=\"What is Julia?\")\nprintln(\"Role: \", msg.role)\n\n# Multimodal input\nparts = [\n    input_text(\"Describe this image:\"),\n    input_image(\"https://example.com/photo.jpg\", detail=\"high\")\n]\nprintln(\"Parts: \", length(parts))\nprintln(\"Part types: \", [p[:type] for p in parts])","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Tool-Types","page":"Responses Types","title":"Tool Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Tool-Constructors","page":"Responses Types","title":"Tool Constructors","text":"# Function tool\nft = function_tool(\"calculate\", \"Evaluate a math expression\",\n    parameters=Dict(\"type\" => \"object\", \"properties\" => Dict(\n        \"expr\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\")\n    ))\n)\nprintln(\"Function tool: \", ft.name)\n\n# Web search\nws = web_search(context_size=\"high\")\nprintln(\"Web search context: \", ws.search_context_size)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Text-Format","page":"Responses Types","title":"Text Format","text":"tf = text_format()\nprintln(\"Default format: \", tf.format.type)\n\njf = json_object_format()\nprintln(\"JSON format: \", jf.format.type)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#Reasoning","page":"Responses Types","title":"Reasoning","text":"reasoning = UniLM.Reasoning(effort=\"high\")\nprintln(\"Effort: \", reasoning.effort)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.Respond","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.Respond","text":"Respond(; model=\"gpt-5.2\", input, kwargs...)\n\nConfiguration struct for an OpenAI Responses API request.\n\nKey Fields\n\nmodel::String: Model to use (default: \"gpt-5.2\")\ninput::Any: A String or Vector{InputMessage} — the prompt input\ninstructions::String: System-level instructions\ntools::Vector: Available tools (FunctionTool, WebSearchTool, FileSearchTool)\nprevious_response_id::String: Chain to a previous response for multi-turn\nreasoning::Reasoning: Reasoning config for O-series models\ntext::TextConfig: Output format (text, json, json_schema)\ntemperature::Float64: Sampling temperature (0.0–2.0), mutually exclusive with top_p\ntop_p::Float64: Nucleus sampling (0.0–1.0), mutually exclusive with temperature\nmax_output_tokens::Int64: Max tokens in the response\nstream::Bool: Enable streaming\ntruncation::String: \"auto\" or \"disabled\"\nstore::Bool: Whether to store the response for later retrieval\nmetadata::AbstractDict: Arbitrary metadata to attach\nuser::String: End-user identifier\n\nExamples\n\n# Simple text\nRespond(input=\"Tell me a joke\")\n\n# With instructions\nRespond(input=\"Translate to French: Hello\", instructions=\"You are a translator\")\n\n# Multi-turn via chaining\nRespond(input=\"Tell me more\", previous_response_id=\"resp_abc123\")\n\n# With tools\nRespond(\n    input=\"What's the weather in NYC?\",\n    tools=ResponseTool[function_tool(\"get_weather\", \"Get weather\", parameters=Dict(\"type\"=>\"object\", \"properties\"=>Dict(\"location\"=>Dict(\"type\"=>\"string\"))))]\n)\n\n# Reasoning (O-series models)\nRespond(input=\"Solve this math problem...\", model=\"o3\", reasoning=Reasoning(effort=\"high\"))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.ResponseObject","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.ResponseObject","text":"ResponseObject\n\nParsed response from the Responses API.\n\nAccessors\n\noutput_text(r) — extract concatenated text output\nfunction_calls(r) — extract function call outputs\nr.id, r.status, r.model — basic metadata\nr.output — full output array (raw dicts)\nr.usage — token usage info\nr.raw — the complete raw JSON dict\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.ResponseSuccess","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.ResponseSuccess","text":"ResponseSuccess <: LLMRequestResponse\n\nSuccessful response from the Responses API. Access the parsed response via .response.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.ResponseFailure","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.ResponseFailure","text":"ResponseFailure <: LLMRequestResponse\n\nHTTP-level failure from the Responses API. Contains the response body and status code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.ResponseCallError","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.ResponseCallError","text":"ResponseCallError <: LLMRequestResponse\n\nException-level error during a Responses API call (network, parsing, etc.).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.output_text","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.output_text","text":"output_text(r::ResponseObject)::String\noutput_text(r::ResponseSuccess)::String\n\nExtract the concatenated text output from a response.\n\nExamples\n\nresult = respond(\"Hello!\")\noutput_text(result)  # => \"Hi there! How can I help?\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.function_calls","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.function_calls","text":"function_calls(r::ResponseObject)::Vector{Dict{String,Any}}\nfunction_calls(r::ResponseSuccess)::Vector{Dict{String,Any}}\n\nExtract function call outputs from a response.\n\nEach dict contains: \"id\", \"call_id\", \"name\", \"arguments\" (JSON string), \"status\".\n\nExamples\n\nresult = respond(\"What's the weather?\", tools=[function_tool(\"get_weather\", ...)])\nfor call in function_calls(result)\n    name = call[\"name\"]\n    args = JSON.parse(call[\"arguments\"])\n    # dispatch to your function...\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.respond","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.respond","text":"respond(r::Respond; retries=0, callback=nothing)\n\nSend a request to the OpenAI Responses API.\n\nReturns ResponseSuccess, ResponseFailure, or ResponseCallError.\n\nFor streaming, set stream=true and pass a callback:\n\ncallback(chunk::Union{String, ResponseObject}, close::Ref{Bool})\n\nExamples\n\nr = Respond(input=\"Tell me a joke\")\nresult = respond(r)\nif result isa ResponseSuccess\n    println(output_text(result))\nend\n\n\n\n\n\nrespond(input; kwargs...)\n\nConvenience method: create a Respond from input + keyword arguments and send it.\n\nExamples\n\n# Simple text\nresult = respond(\"Tell me a joke\")\n\n# With instructions and model\nresult = respond(\"Translate: Hello\", instructions=\"You are a translator\", model=\"gpt-5.2\")\n\n# With tools\nresult = respond(\"Search for Julia news\", tools=[web_search()])\n\n# Multi-turn\nr1 = respond(\"Tell me a joke\")\nr2 = respond(\"Tell me another\", previous_response_id=r1.response.id)\n\n# Streaming\nrespond(\"Tell me a story\", stream=true) do chunk, close\n    if chunk isa String\n        print(chunk)  # partial text delta\n    end\nend\n\n\n\n\n\nrespond(callback::Function, input; kwargs...)\n\ndo-block form for streaming. Automatically sets stream=true.\n\nExamples\n\nrespond(\"Tell me a story\") do chunk, close\n    if chunk isa String\n        print(chunk)\n    elseif chunk isa ResponseObject\n        println(\"\\nDone! Status: \", chunk.status)\n    end\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.get_response","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.get_response","text":"get_response(response_id::String; service=OPENAIServiceEndpoint)\n\nRetrieve an existing response by its ID.\n\nExamples\n\nresult = get_response(\"resp_abc123\")\nif result isa ResponseSuccess\n    println(output_text(result))\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.delete_response","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.delete_response","text":"delete_response(response_id::String; service=OPENAIServiceEndpoint)\n\nDelete a stored response by its ID. Returns a Dict with \"id\", \"object\", \"deleted\" keys.\n\nExamples\n\nresult = delete_response(\"resp_abc123\")\nresult[\"deleted\"]  # => true\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.list_input_items","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.list_input_items","text":"list_input_items(response_id::String; limit=20, order=\"desc\", after=nothing, service=OPENAIServiceEndpoint)\n\nList input items for a stored response. Returns a Dict with \"data\", \"first_id\", \"last_id\", \"has_more\".\n\nExamples\n\nitems = list_input_items(\"resp_abc123\")\nfor item in items[\"data\"]\n    println(item[\"type\"], \": \", item)\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.InputMessage","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.InputMessage","text":"InputMessage(; role, content)\n\nA structured input message for the Responses API.\n\nFields\n\nrole::String: \"user\", \"assistant\", \"system\", or \"developer\"\ncontent::Any: String or a vector of content parts (see input_text, input_image, input_file)\n\nExamples\n\nInputMessage(role=\"user\", content=\"What is 2+2?\")\nInputMessage(role=\"user\", content=[input_text(\"Describe this:\"), input_image(\"https://example.com/img.png\")])\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.input_text","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.input_text","text":"input_text(text::String)\n\nCreate an input_text content part for multimodal input messages.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.input_image","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.input_image","text":"input_image(url::String; detail=nothing)\n\nCreate an input_image content part. detail can be \"auto\", \"low\", or \"high\".\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.input_file","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.input_file","text":"input_file(; url=nothing, id=nothing)\n\nCreate an input_file content part. Provide either a url or a file_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.ResponseTool","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.ResponseTool","text":"ResponseTool\n\nAbstract supertype for Responses API tools. Subtypes:\n\nFunctionTool\nWebSearchTool\nFileSearchTool\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.FunctionTool","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.FunctionTool","text":"FunctionTool(; name, description=nothing, parameters=nothing, strict=nothing)\n\nA function tool for the Responses API.\n\nExamples\n\nFunctionTool(\n    name=\"get_weather\",\n    description=\"Get current weather for a location\",\n    parameters=Dict(\n        \"type\" => \"object\",\n        \"properties\" => Dict(\n            \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"description\" => \"City name\")\n        ),\n        \"required\" => [\"location\"]\n    )\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.WebSearchTool","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.WebSearchTool","text":"WebSearchTool(; search_context_size=\"medium\", user_location=nothing)\n\nA web search tool for the Responses API. Allows the model to search the web.\n\nsearch_context_size: \"low\", \"medium\", or \"high\"\nuser_location: Dict with keys like \"country\", \"city\", \"region\", \"timezone\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.FileSearchTool","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.FileSearchTool","text":"FileSearchTool(; vector_store_ids, max_num_results=nothing, ranking_options=nothing, filters=nothing)\n\nA file search tool for the Responses API. Searches over uploaded vector stores.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.function_tool","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.function_tool","text":"function_tool(name, description=nothing; parameters=nothing, strict=nothing)\n\nShorthand constructor for FunctionTool.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.web_search","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.web_search","text":"web_search(; context_size=\"medium\", location=nothing)\n\nShorthand constructor for WebSearchTool.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.file_search","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.file_search","text":"file_search(store_ids::Vector{String}; max_results=nothing, ranking=nothing, filters=nothing)\n\nShorthand constructor for FileSearchTool.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.TextConfig","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.TextConfig","text":"TextConfig(; format=TextFormatSpec())\n\nWrapper for the text field in the Responses API request body.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.TextFormatSpec","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.TextFormatSpec","text":"TextFormatSpec(; type=\"text\", name=nothing, description=nothing, schema=nothing, strict=nothing)\n\nOutput text format specification.\n\ntype: \"text\" (default), \"json_object\", or \"json_schema\"\nFor \"json_schema\": provide name, description, schema, and optionally strict\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.text_format","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.text_format","text":"text_format(; kwargs...)\n\nCreate a TextConfig with the given format options.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.json_schema_format","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.json_schema_format","text":"json_schema_format(name, description, schema; strict=nothing)\n\nCreate a JSON Schema output format for structured output.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.json_object_format","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.json_object_format","text":"json_object_format()\n\nCreate a JSON object output format (unstructured).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/responses/#UniLM.Reasoning","page":"Responses Types","title":"UniLM.Reasoning","text":"Reasoning(; effort=nothing, summary=nothing)\n\nReasoning configuration for O-series models (o3, o4-mini, etc.).\n\neffort: \"low\", \"medium\", or \"high\"\nsummary: \"auto\", \"concise\", or \"detailed\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"_generated/respond_instructions/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> result = respond(\n           \"Translate to French: The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.\",\n           instructions=\"You are a professional translator. Respond only with the translation.\"\n       )\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Le rapide renard brun saute par-dessus le chien paresseux.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_json/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", response_format=ResponseFormat())\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You always respond in valid JSON.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"List 3 programming languages with their year of creation.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> JSON.parse(result.message.content)\n{\n  \"languages\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Python\",\n      \"year\": 1991\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Java\",\n      \"year\": 1995\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n      \"year\": 1995\n    }\n  ]\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/respond_multiturn/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> r1 = respond(\"Tell me a one-liner programming joke.\", instructions=\"Be concise.\")\n\njulia> output_text(r1)\n\"There are only 10 kinds of people in the world: those who understand binary and those who don’t.\"\n\njulia> r2 = respond(\"Explain why that's funny, in one sentence.\", previous_response_id=r1.response.id)\n\njulia> output_text(r2)\n\"It’s funny because “10” looks like ten in decimal but equals two in binary, so it sets up a nerdy misdirection that only people who know binary immediately get.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/respond_streaming/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> task = respond(\"Write a haiku about Julia programming.\") do chunk, close\n           if chunk isa String\n               print(chunk)  # tokens stream in real-time\n           elseif chunk isa ResponseObject\n               println(\"\\nDone! Status: \", chunk.status)\n           end\n       end\nMultiple dispatch sings,  \nTypes align in swift fusion—  \nLoops bloom into speed.\nDone! Status: completed\n\njulia> result = fetch(task)\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Multiple dispatch sings,  \\nTypes align in swift fusion—  \\nLoops bloom into speed.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/respond_function_call/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> weather_tool = function_tool(\n           \"get_weather\", \"Get the current weather for a given location\",\n           parameters=Dict(\n               \"type\" => \"object\",\n               \"properties\" => Dict(\n                   \"location\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"description\" => \"City name\"),\n                   \"unit\" => Dict(\"type\" => \"string\", \"enum\" => [\"celsius\", \"fahrenheit\"])\n               ),\n               \"required\" => [\"location\", \"unit\"],\n               \"additionalProperties\" => false\n           ),\n           strict=true\n       )\n\njulia> result = respond(\"What's the weather in Tokyo? Use celsius.\", tools=[weather_tool])\n\njulia> calls = function_calls(result)\n\njulia> calls[1][\"name\"]\n\"get_weather\"\n\njulia> JSON.parse(calls[1][\"arguments\"])\n{\n  \"location\": \"Tokyo\",\n  \"unit\": \"celsius\"\n}","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_multiturn/","page":"Example usages:","title":"Example usages:","text":"julia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Give a short Julia code example of it.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> println(result.message.content)\nHere’s a simple example of multiple dispatch in Julia:\n\n\njulia function area(shape::Tuple{Symbol, Float64})     if shape[1] == :circle         return π * shape[2]^2     elseif shape[1] == :rectangle         return shape[2] * shape[3]     end end","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_multiturn/#Example-usages:","page":"Example usages:","title":"Example usages:","text":"circlearea = area(:circle, 5.0)           # Area of a circle with radius 5 rectanglearea = area(:rectangle, 4.0, 6.0) # Area of a rectangle 4x6\n\nprintln(\"Circle Area: \", circlearea) println(\"Rectangle Area: \", rectanglearea)\n\n\nIn this example, the `area` function behaves differently depending on the shape type (`:circle` or `:rectangle`) and its corresponding dimensions.\n\njulia> length(chat)  # system + user + assistant + user + assistant\n5","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/respond_websearch/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> result = respond(\n           \"What is the latest stable release of the Julia programming language?\",\n           tools=[web_search()]\n       )\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"The latest **stable** release of the Julia programming language is **Julia v1.12.5**. ([julialang.org](https://julialang.org/))\"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Result-Types","page":"Result Types","title":"Result Types","text":"Abstract and concrete types for handling API call outcomes. All result types are subtypes of LLMRequestResponse.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Abstract-Type","page":"Result Types","title":"Abstract Type","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Chat-Completions-Results","page":"Result Types","title":"Chat Completions Results","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Pattern-Matching","page":"Result Types","title":"Pattern Matching","text":"result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\nif result isa LLMSuccess\n    println(result.message.content)\n    println(result.message.finish_reason)  # \"stop\"\nelseif result isa LLMFailure\n    @warn \"HTTP $(result.status): $(result.response)\"\nelseif result isa LLMCallError\n    @error \"Call error: $(result.error)\"\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Responses-API-Results","page":"Result Types","title":"Responses API Results","text":"See also the Responses API reference.\n\nResponseSuccess\nResponseFailure\nResponseCallError","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Pattern-Matching-2","page":"Result Types","title":"Pattern Matching","text":"result = respond(\"Tell me a joke\")\n\nif result isa ResponseSuccess\n    println(output_text(result))\n    println(result.response.status)  # \"completed\"\nelseif result isa ResponseFailure\n    @warn \"HTTP $(result.status)\"\nelseif result isa ResponseCallError\n    @error result.error\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Image-Generation-Results","page":"Result Types","title":"Image Generation Results","text":"See also the Images API reference.\n\nImageSuccess\nImageFailure\nImageCallError","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Pattern-Matching-3","page":"Result Types","title":"Pattern Matching","text":"result = generate_image(\"A robot writing Julia code\")\n\nif result isa ImageSuccess\n    save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot.png\")\nelseif result isa ImageFailure\n    @warn \"HTTP $(result.status): $(result.response)\"\nelseif result isa ImageCallError\n    @error result.error\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#Type-Hierarchy","page":"Result Types","title":"Type Hierarchy","text":"All result types share the abstract parent LLMRequestResponse:\n\nLLMRequestResponse\n├── LLMSuccess          (Chat Completions)\n├── LLMFailure          (Chat Completions)\n├── LLMCallError        (Chat Completions)\n├── ResponseSuccess     (Responses API)\n├── ResponseFailure     (Responses API)\n├── ResponseCallError   (Responses API)\n├── ImageSuccess        (Image Generation)\n├── ImageFailure        (Image Generation)\n└── ImageCallError      (Image Generation)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/results/#UniLM.LLMRequestResponse","page":"Result Types","title":"UniLM.LLMRequestResponse","text":"LLMRequestResponse\n\nAbstract supertype for all API call results. Pattern-match on subtypes to handle outcomes:\n\nLLMSuccess — successful response\nLLMFailure — HTTP-level failure (non-200 status)\nLLMCallError — exception during the call (network error, etc.)\nResponseSuccess — successful Responses API result\nResponseFailure — Responses API HTTP failure\nResponseCallError — Responses API exception\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/results/#UniLM.LLMSuccess","page":"Result Types","title":"UniLM.LLMSuccess","text":"LLMSuccess(; message, self)\n\nSuccessful Chat Completions API response.\n\nFields\n\nmessage::Message: The assistant's reply message.\nself::Chat: The updated Chat object (with the new message appended if history=true).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/results/#UniLM.LLMFailure","page":"Result Types","title":"UniLM.LLMFailure","text":"LLMFailure(; response, status, self)\n\nHTTP-level failure from the Chat Completions API. The server returned a non-200 status.\n\nFields\n\nresponse::String: The raw response body.\nstatus::Int: The HTTP status code.\nself::Chat: The Chat object (unchanged).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/results/#UniLM.LLMCallError","page":"Result Types","title":"UniLM.LLMCallError","text":"LLMCallError(; error, status=nothing, self)\n\nException-level error during a Chat Completions API call (network failure, JSON parse error, etc.).\n\nFields\n\nerror::String: The stringified exception.\nstatus::Union{Int,Nothing}: HTTP status if available.\nself::Chat: The Chat object (unchanged).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"getting_started/#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Prerequisites","page":"Getting Started","title":"Prerequisites","text":"Julia 1.12+ (as specified in Project.toml)\nAn OpenAI API key (or Azure/Gemini credentials for those backends)","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Installation","page":"Getting Started","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/algunion/UniLM.jl\")","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Configuration","page":"Getting Started","title":"Configuration","text":"UniLM.jl reads API credentials from environment variables. Set them before making any requests:","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#OpenAI-(default)","page":"Getting Started","title":"OpenAI (default)","text":"ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"] = \"sk-...\"\n\nOr via your shell:\n\nexport OPENAI_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Azure-OpenAI","page":"Getting Started","title":"Azure OpenAI","text":"export AZURE_OPENAI_BASE_URL=\"https://your-resource.openai.azure.com\"\nexport AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=\"your-key\"\nexport AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=\"2024-02-01\"\nexport AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOY_NAME_GPT_5_2=\"your-gpt52-deployment\"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Google-Gemini","page":"Getting Started","title":"Google Gemini","text":"export GEMINI_API_KEY=\"your-gemini-key\"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Your-First-Request","page":"Getting Started","title":"Your First Request","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Using-the-Responses-API","page":"Getting Started","title":"Using the Responses API","text":"The simplest way to get started — one function call:\n\njulia> using UniLM\n\njulia> result = respond(\"Explain Julia's type system in 3 bullet points\")\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Julia's multiple dispatch means a function can have many method definitions, and Julia chooses which one to run based on the types of *all* arguments in a call (not just the first). This makes it easy to write generic code while still getting specialized, high-performance behavior for specific type combinations.\"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Using-Chat-Completions","page":"Getting Started","title":"Using Chat Completions","text":"For stateful, multi-turn conversations:\n\njulia> using UniLM\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\")\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a concise Julia programming tutor.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What is multiple dispatch? Answer in 2-3 sentences.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"Multiple dispatch is a feature in programming languages, including Julia, that allows the selection of a method to execute based on the types of all its arguments, rather than just the first one. This enables more flexible and expressive code, as it can define different behaviors for a function depending on the combination of argument types. It supports polymorphism, making it easier to write generic code that works with multiple types.\"\n\njulia> result.message.finish_reason\n\"stop\"\n\njulia> length(chat)  # system + user + assistant\n3","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Generating-Images","page":"Getting Started","title":"Generating Images","text":"julia> result = generate_image(\n           \"A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book\",\n           size=\"1024x1024\", quality=\"medium\"\n       )\n\njulia> result isa ImageSuccess\ntrue\n\njulia> length(image_data(result))\n1\n\njulia> save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot_julia.png\")\n\"robot_julia.png\"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Using-Keyword-Arguments","page":"Getting Started","title":"Using Keyword Arguments","text":"For one-shot requests without managing Chat objects:\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(\n           systemprompt=\"You are a calculator. Respond only with the number.\",\n           userprompt=\"What is 42 * 17?\",\n           model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n           temperature=0.0\n       )\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"714\"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#Handling-Results","page":"Getting Started","title":"Handling Results","text":"All API calls return subtypes of LLMRequestResponse. Use Julia's pattern matching:\n\nusing UniLM\nusing InteractiveUtils\n\n# Construct a chat to show the result type hierarchy\nchat = Chat()\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are helpful.\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Hello!\"))\n\n# Show the type hierarchy:\nprintln(\"LLMRequestResponse subtypes:\")\nfor T in subtypes(UniLM.LLMRequestResponse)\n    println(\"  \", T)\nend\n\nresult = chatrequest!(chat)\n\nif result isa LLMSuccess\n    println(\"Assistant: \", result.message.content)\n    println(\"Finish reason: \", result.message.finish_reason)\nelseif result isa LLMFailure\n    @warn \"API returned HTTP $(result.status): $(result.response)\"\nelseif result isa LLMCallError\n    @error \"Call failed: $(result.error)\"\nend\n\nFor the Responses API:\n\nresult = respond(\"Hello!\")\n\nif result isa ResponseSuccess\n    println(output_text(result))\n    println(\"Status: \", result.response.status)  # \"completed\"\n    println(\"Model: \", result.response.model)\nelseif result isa ResponseFailure\n    @warn \"HTTP $(result.status)\"\nelseif result isa ResponseCallError\n    @error result.error\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"getting_started/#What's-Next?","page":"Getting Started","title":"What's Next?","text":"Want to... Read...\nBuild multi-turn conversations Chat Completions Guide\nUse the newer Responses API Responses API Guide\nGenerate images from prompts Image Generation Guide\nCall functions from the model Tool Calling Guide\nStream tokens in real-time Streaming Guide\nGet structured JSON output Structured Output Guide\nUse Azure or Gemini Multi-Backend Guide","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_kwargs/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> result = chatrequest!(\n           systemprompt=\"You are a calculator. Respond only with the number.\",\n           userprompt=\"What is 42 * 17?\",\n           model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n           temperature=0.0\n       )\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"714\"","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_streaming/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", stream=true)\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a poet.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Write a very short 2-line poem about coding.\"))\n\njulia> task = chatrequest!(chat, callback=function(chunk, close)\n           if chunk isa String\n               print(chunk)  # tokens stream in real-time\n           elseif chunk isa Message\n               println(\"\\n--- done ---\")\n           end\n       end)\nIn lines of logic, dreams arise,  \nCrafting worlds behind the screen's wise guise\n--- done ---\n\njulia> msg, _ = fetch(task)\n\njulia> msg.content\n\"In lines of logic, dreams arise,  \\nCrafting worlds behind the screen's wise guise\"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Service-Endpoints","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Service Endpoints","text":"Types for configuring multi-backend service endpoints.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Abstract-Type","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Abstract Type","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Endpoint-Types","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Endpoint Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Configuration","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Configuration","text":"Each endpoint reads its configuration from environment variables:","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#OpenAI-(default)","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"OpenAI (default)","text":"Variable Description\nOPENAI_API_KEY Your OpenAI API key","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Azure-OpenAI","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Azure OpenAI","text":"Variable Description\nAZURE_OPENAI_BASE_URL Azure endpoint base URL\nAZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY Azure API key\nAZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION API version (e.g. 2024-12-01-preview)\nAZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOY_NAME_GPT_5_2 Deployment name for gpt-5.2","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Google-Gemini","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Google Gemini","text":"Variable Description\nGEMINI_API_KEY Your Gemini API key","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Azure-Deployment-Mapping","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Azure Deployment Mapping","text":"Azure requires model-to-deployment name mappings. Use add_azure_deploy_name! to register custom mappings:\n\nusing UniLM\n\n# Register a custom deployment for a specific model\nUniLM.add_azure_deploy_name!(\"gpt-5.2\", \"my-gpt52-deploy\")\nprintln(\"Registered deployment: \", UniLM._MODEL_ENDPOINTS_AZURE_OPENAI[\"gpt-5.2\"])","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#Selecting-a-Backend","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"Selecting a Backend","text":"Pass the service keyword to any request constructor:\n\nchat = Chat(service=UniLM.AZUREServiceEndpoint, model=\"gpt-5.2\")\nprintln(\"Service: \", chat.service)\nprintln(\"Model: \", chat.model)","category":"section"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#UniLM.ServiceEndpoint","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"UniLM.ServiceEndpoint","text":"ServiceEndpoint\n\nAbstract supertype for LLM service backends. Subtypes control URL routing and authentication.\n\nSubtypes:\n\nOPENAIServiceEndpoint — OpenAI API (default)\nAZUREServiceEndpoint — Azure OpenAI Service\nGEMINIServiceEndpoint — Google Gemini via OpenAI-compatible endpoint\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#UniLM.OPENAIServiceEndpoint","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"UniLM.OPENAIServiceEndpoint","text":"OpenAI API service endpoint (default). Requires OPENAI_API_KEY env variable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#UniLM.AZUREServiceEndpoint","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"UniLM.AZUREServiceEndpoint","text":"Azure OpenAI Service endpoint. Requires AZURE_OPENAI_BASE_URL, AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY, and AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION env variables.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/endpoints/#UniLM.GEMINIServiceEndpoint","page":"Service Endpoints","title":"UniLM.GEMINIServiceEndpoint","text":"Google Gemini endpoint (OpenAI-compatible). Requires GEMINI_API_KEY env variable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#UniLM.jl","page":"Home","title":"UniLM.jl","text":"A unified Julia interface for large language models.\n\n(Image: Coverage Status) (Image: )","category":"section"},{"location":"#What-is-UniLM.jl?","page":"Home","title":"What is UniLM.jl?","text":"UniLM.jl provides a Julian, type-safe interface to OpenAI's language models — covering both the classic Chat Completions API, the newer Responses API, and the Image Generation API. It aims to become a unified solution for accessing multiple LLM providers from Julia.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Key-Features","page":"Home","title":"Key Features","text":"🗣️ Chat Completions — stateful conversations with automatic history management\n🔮 Responses API — OpenAI's newer API with built-in tools, multi-turn chaining, and reasoning\n🖼️ Image Generation — create images from text prompts with gpt-image-1.5\n🔧 Tool/Function Calling — first-class support for function tools in both APIs\n📊 Embeddings — text embedding generation\n🌊 Streaming — real-time token streaming with do-block syntax\n📐 Structured Output — JSON Schema–constrained generation\n☁️ Multi-Backend — OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, and Google Gemini\n✅ Type Safety — invalid states are unrepresentable; tested with JET.jl and Aqua.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"#Two-APIs,-One-Package","page":"Home","title":"Two APIs, One Package","text":"Feature Chat Completions Responses API\nStateful conversations Chat + push! previous_response_id\nSystem prompt Message(Val(:system), ...) instructions kwarg\nTool calling GPTTool / GPTToolCall FunctionTool / function_tool\nWeb search ✗ WebSearchTool\nFile search ✗ FileSearchTool\nStreaming stream=true + callback do-block syntax\nStructured output ResponseFormat TextConfig / json_schema_format\nReasoning (O-series) ✗ Reasoning","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/algunion/UniLM.jl\")\n\nOr in the Pkg REPL:\n\npkg> add https://github.com/algunion/UniLM.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quick-Example","page":"Home","title":"Quick Example","text":"Building requests — these construct objects locally without calling the API:\n\nusing UniLM\nusing JSON\n\n# Chat Completions request\nchat = Chat(model=\"gpt-5.2\")\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a Julia expert.\"))\npush!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Explain multiple dispatch in one sentence.\"))\nprintln(\"Chat has \", length(chat), \" messages, model: \", chat.model)\nprintln(\"Request body preview:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(chat))\n\n# Responses API request\nr = Respond(input=\"What makes Julia special?\")\nprintln(\"Respond model: \", r.model)\nprintln(JSON.json(r))\n\n# Image Generation request\nig = ImageGeneration(prompt=\"A watercolor Julia logo\", quality=\"high\")\nprintln(\"Image model: \", ig.model)\nprintln(JSON.json(ig))\n\nWith a valid API key, actual API calls return structured results:\n\nResponses API (recommended for new code):\n\njulia> result = respond(\"Explain Julia's multiple dispatch in 2-3 sentences.\")\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Julia's multiple dispatch means a function can have many method definitions, and Julia chooses which one to run based on the types of *all* arguments in a call (not just the first). This makes it easy to write generic code while still getting specialized, high-performance behavior for specific type combinations.\"\n\nChat Completions:\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\")\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a concise Julia programming tutor.\"))\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What is multiple dispatch? Answer in 2-3 sentences.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"Multiple dispatch is a feature in programming languages, including Julia, that allows the selection of a method to execute based on the types of all its arguments, rather than just the first one. This enables more flexible and expressive code, as it can define different behaviors for a function depending on the combination of argument types. It supports polymorphism, making it easier to write generic code that works with multiple types.\"\n\nImage Generation:\n\njulia> result = generate_image(\n           \"A watercolor painting of a friendly robot reading a Julia programming book\",\n           size=\"1024x1024\", quality=\"medium\"\n       )\n\njulia> result isa ImageSuccess\ntrue\n\njulia> save_image(image_data(result)[1], \"robot_julia.png\")\n\"robot_julia.png\"\n\n(Image: Generated robot reading Julia)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Next-Steps","page":"Home","title":"Next Steps","text":"Getting Started — setup and first requests\nChat Completions Guide — deep dive into Chat and chatrequest!\nResponses API Guide — the newer Responses API\nImage Generation Guide — create images from text prompts\nAPI Reference — full type and function reference","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/streaming/#streaming_guide","page":"Streaming","title":"Streaming","text":"Both APIs support real-time streaming of generated tokens, so you can display partial results as they arrive.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/streaming/#Chat-Completions-Streaming","page":"Streaming","title":"Chat Completions Streaming","text":"Set stream=true and provide a callback:\n\njulia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", stream=true)\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a poet.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"Write a very short 2-line poem about coding.\"))\n\njulia> task = chatrequest!(chat, callback=function(chunk, close)\n           if chunk isa String\n               print(chunk)  # tokens stream in real-time\n           elseif chunk isa Message\n               println(\"\\n--- done ---\")\n           end\n       end)\nIn lines of logic, dreams arise,  \nCrafting worlds behind the screen's wise guise\n--- done ---\n\njulia> msg, _ = fetch(task)\n\njulia> msg.content\n\"In lines of logic, dreams arise,  \\nCrafting worlds behind the screen's wise guise\"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/streaming/#Stopping-a-Stream-Early","page":"Streaming","title":"Stopping a Stream Early","text":"The callback receives a Ref{Bool} that you can set to true to stop streaming:\n\ntask = chatrequest!(chat, callback=function(chunk, close)\n    if chunk isa String\n        print(chunk)\n        if contains(chunk, \"bad word\")\n            close[] = true  # stop the stream\n        end\n    end\nend)","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/streaming/#Responses-API-Streaming","page":"Streaming","title":"Responses API Streaming","text":"The Responses API provides an even cleaner streaming interface using Julia's do-block syntax:\n\njulia> task = respond(\"Write a haiku about Julia programming.\") do chunk, close\n           if chunk isa String\n               print(chunk)  # tokens stream in real-time\n           elseif chunk isa ResponseObject\n               println(\"\\nDone! Status: \", chunk.status)\n           end\n       end\nMultiple dispatch sings,  \nTypes align in swift fusion—  \nLoops bloom into speed.\nDone! Status: completed\n\njulia> result = fetch(task)\n\njulia> output_text(result)\n\"Multiple dispatch sings,  \\nTypes align in swift fusion—  \\nLoops bloom into speed.\"\n\nThe do-block form automatically sets stream=true.","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/streaming/#With-Explicit-Configuration","page":"Streaming","title":"With Explicit Configuration","text":"using UniLM\nusing JSON\n\nr = Respond(\n    input=\"Explain quantum computing step by step\",\n    model=\"gpt-5.2\",\n    stream=true,\n    max_output_tokens=2000,\n)\nprintln(\"Stream enabled: \", r.stream)\nprintln(\"Request preview:\")\nprintln(JSON.json(r))","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/streaming/#Notes","page":"Streaming","title":"Notes","text":"Streaming runs on a separate Julia thread via Threads.@spawn. Make sure Julia is started with multiple threads (julia -t auto).\nThe returned Task can be fetched to get the final result.\nThe close Ref{Bool} can be set to true from the callback to terminate the stream early.\nOn completion, the Chat Completions callback receives a Message; the Responses API callback receives a ResponseObject.","category":"section"},{"location":"_generated/chat_basic/","page":"-","title":"-","text":"julia> chat = Chat(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\")\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:system), \"You are a concise Julia programming tutor.\"))\n\njulia> push!(chat, Message(Val(:user), \"What is multiple dispatch? Answer in 2-3 sentences.\"))\n\njulia> result = chatrequest!(chat)\n\njulia> result.message.content\n\"Multiple dispatch is a feature in programming languages, including Julia, that allows the selection of a method to execute based on the types of all its arguments, rather than just the first one. This enables more flexible and expressive code, as it can define different behaviors for a function depending on the combination of argument types. It supports polymorphism, making it easier to write generic code that works with multiple types.\"\n\njulia> result.message.finish_reason\n\"stop\"\n\njulia> length(chat)  # system + user + assistant\n3","category":"section"}]
}
